INSERT INTO `superheroes` (`Title`, `ID`, `Alignment`, `Gender`, `Height`, `Weight`, `Identity`, `MaritalStatus`, `Eyes`, `Hair`, `PlaceOfBirth`, `PlaceOfDeath`, `Citizenship`, `Occupation`) VALUES
('Hope Summers', '119275', 'Good', 'Female', '5\'6\'\'\n| Weight                  = 106 lbs\n| Eyes                    = Green\n| Hair                    = Red\n| UnusualFeatures         = Has shown having irises in the form of the Phoenix\n\n| Citizenship             = American\n| MaritalStatus           = Single\n| Occupation              = Adventurer; former nomad\n| Education               = Tutored by [[Nathan Summers (Earth-616)|Cable]]\n\n| Origin                  = [[Homo superior|Mutant]]\n| PlaceOfBirth            = Cooperstown Memorial Hospital, [[Cooperstown]], [[Alaska]]\n| Creators                = Mike Carey; Chris Bachalo\n| First                   = X-Men Vol 2 205\n\n| HistoryText             = \n[[File:Nathan Summers (Earth-616) with baby Hope Summers (Earth-616) 001.jpg|thumb|left|150px|[[Nathan Summers (Earth-616)|Cable]] escaping with the mutant infant]]\n\n===[[X-Men: Messiah Complex|Messiah CompleX]]===\n\'\'\'Hope\'\'\' was the first new mutant born since the [[Decimation|M-Day]]. The moment she was born, [[Cerebra (Mutant Detector)|Cerebra]] blew up. Soon after her birthplace in [[Cooperstown]], [[Alaska]] was attacked by the [[Purifiers (Earth-616)|Purifiers]], who had used information given from the time-traveling [[Sentinel]] [[Nimrod (Earth-811)|Nimrod]] warning them of her arrival. Although everyone else in town was murdered by the Purifiers, [[Nathan Summers (Earth-616)|Cable]] managed to save her. According to him, the baby was the messiah supposed to save both [[Homo superior|mutants]] and [[Homo sapiens|humankind]]. However, according to the Purifiers and [[Lucas Bishop (Earth-1191)|Bishop]], she would become an evil antichrist and kill a million humans within six minutes, turning humanity against mutants once again, thus leading into a new era of mutant persecution, the very [[Earth-1191|timeline]] in which Bishop was born.\n\nThe baby was later kidnapped from Cable by the [[Marauders (Earth-616)|Marauders]] and delivered to [[Nathaniel Essex (Earth-616)|Mister Sinister]] who was actually [[Raven Darkholme (Earth-616)|Mystique]] in disguise. She took the baby and made her touch the comatose [[Rogue (Anna Marie) (Earth-616)|Rogue]]. [[Remy LeBeau (Earth-616)|Gambit]] quickly took her away from Mystique, believing that she just killed her but he was amazed to see that the baby was alright and that it even cured Rogue of the Strain 88 virus. After a huge battle between the Marauders, [[X-Men (Earth-616)|X-Men]], and [[Predator X (Earth-616)|Predator X]], [[Scott Summers (Earth-616)|Cyclops]] decided that the baby would be better off with Cable, and allowed his son to take her to the [[Earth-80521|future]]. However, an adamant Bishop decided to track Cable and the baby in order to finally kill her and prevent [[Earth-1191|his future]] from happening.\n\n===Into the [[Earth-4935|Future]]===\nUpon jumping into the future, Cable took her to the secluded safe haven of [[Earth-80521#New Liberty|New Liberty]] in the future, where Cable married a fellow civilian named [[Hope Summers (Earth-80521)|Hope]], who became like a mother to the mutant baby. Years passed, since his last battle with Bishop damaged his time machine, Cable could only jump forward in time. She was now seven years old. But then New Liberty was invaded by humanoid insects who called themselves the United States Army. Cable fought them and left New Liberty with his wife and Hope in order to make sure New Liberty didn\'t fall. After spending months in the wasteland, the family was attacked by the president of the insects, whom Hope managed to save her family from by stabbing the insect in his weak spot, since she had been watching Cable fight. Cable questioned the president where he found out that Bishop, in order to find Hope in the future, had destroyed all the continents in the world, except North America, in order to easily find her and kill her. Cable killed the president, and the family moved on. The family encountered a settlement, but were met with resistance. Cable took care of them easily, but not fast enough, as her mother was shot and died in Cable\'s arms while she watched. Hope saw Cable bury her mother and departed with him. After arriving at a church, the pastor asked the name of the child. In that moment, Cable decided to name her \'\'\'Hope Summers\'\'\', in honor of her adoptive mother.\n\n[[File:Hope Summers (Earth-616).jpg|thumb|left|150px|A young Hope Summers.]]\n===[[Messiah War]]===\nHope later became the center of another conflict, this time between [[Nathan Summers (Earth-616)|Cable]], [[Nathan Summers (Stryfe) (Earth-4935)|Stryfe]], and [[X-Force (Strike Team) (Earth-616)|X-Force]]. Hope was kidnapped by Stryfe who was working with Bishop. She watched as Stryfe tortured [[James Proudstar (Earth-616)|Warpath]] until Cable, [[James Howlett (Earth-616)|Wolverine]], and [[Joshua Foley (Earth-616)|Elixir]] came to their rescue. In the following fight she survived along with the rest of the X-Force and Cable with Bishop losing an eye to Wolverine and having his time travel device damaged. When Cable and Hope were forced to time travel again, Hope resisted because she wanted to stay with [[Laura Kinney (Earth-616)|X-23]] and Elixir, with whom she had bonded during the War. That caused her to kick Cable in mid jump stranding herself and Cable two years apart from each other.\n\n[[File:Hope Summers (Earth-616) and Emil.jpg|thumb|right|150px|Hope and Emil on the \'\'Ensabahnur I\'\']]\n===Stranded===\nHope fled the rubble of Stryfe\'s Celestial City and befriended [[Emil Spence (Earth-80521)|Emil Spence]], the descendant of Stryfe\'s warriors, Stryfetroopers. Hope survived for two years, with the help of Emil, until rejoining Cable and fleeing Earth on the second last spaceship on the planet, the \'\'[[Ensabahnur I]]\'\', which Cable commandeered posing as Stryfe. Hope was devastated at being forced to leave Emil, the boy she loved.\n\nAt some point during their journey Hope accidentally revealed Cable\'s true identity, and he was imprisoned. Bishop and Emil eventually caught up to Cable and Hope, Emil under the impression that Cable had kidnapped Hope and Bishop was her true father, Bishop was also armed with a thermo-nuclear device which he planned to activate as soon as he saw Hope. While Bishop and Emil raided the \'\'Ensahabnur I\'\', Emil and Hope were reunited and Hope explained to Emil that Bishop was in fact trying to kill her.\n\nDuring Bishop\'s invasion, the [[Brood (Race)|Brood]], attracted to Hope\'s power, attacked both ships, distracting Bishop from Hope. While Cable and Bishop both fought the Brood, Hope and Emil made their way to the ship\'s two terraforming pods, which would facilitate their escape. Emil placed Hope in the pod against her will as she refused to leave Cable. As Emil was preparing the second pod Cable appeared and Emil gave the second pod to Cable, sacrificing his own life.\n\nAfter Cable and Hope had left, Emil obtained Bishops thermo-nuclear weapon, detonating moments before he could be attacked by a Sleazoid. However, Bishop escaped by allowing himself to be absorbed by an [[Acanti]], and two years later he had tracked Hope and Cable in cryo-sleep within their terraforming pods.\n\n===Homecoming===\nHope and Cable survived the brutal crash-landing back onto the [[Earth-80521|dying Earth]]. Hope and Cable make encampment in ruins infest with mutant rats.{{r|X-Men: Hope #1}} Soon Hope made the decision that she was ready to go [[Earth-616|home]] and join the [[X-Men (Earth-616)|X-Men]]. However, the only fully functioning time machine in Bishop\'s robotic arm, and Bishop is still trapped inside a dying Acanti. Cable blows up the Acanti corpse, awakes Bishop and narrowly escapes with Hope into the past, but not before Bishop fires a bullet point blank at Hope\'s head. Fortunately, Hope mutant powers manifested and she used Cable\'s [[telekinesis]] to stop the bullet in midair.{{r|Cable Vol 2 21}}\n\nThe cobbled together time machine turned out to be somewhat faulty, making it difficult to time-sliding to a specific date. Also, the remnants of Bishop time device were triggered with each jump which allowed him to follow Cable and anywhere in time. A violent chase ensues across numerous time periods on [[Manhattan|Manhattan Island]] including Revolutionary War and ruins of the apocalyptic future.{{r|Cable Vol 2 22}} Suddenly, they arrive in 2044 where Cable and Hope were briefly reunited with [[Sophie Pettit (Earth-80521)|Sophie Pettit]]. However, Bishop also met some former comrades, [[Turnpike Authority (Earth-80521)|Turnpike Authority]], and begins chasing Hope with his new reinforcements. Unfortunately, during the chase, the car carrying Cable, Hope and Sophie crashed in [[Central Park]]. Cable was able to save Hope and time-jump, but Sophie died. Hope and Cable land in Central Park of 1933 and waste no time in moving before Bishop follows.{{r|Cable Vol 2 23}} Cable and Hope made several more rapid time jumps, each time over shooting their true destination, but each time getting closer. Bishop finally reach them and was almost successful in killing Hope until Cable activated the time device in his arm to send Bishop to the year 6700 AD. Finally free of their pursuer, Hope and Cable borrow a car and drive to the [[Xavier\'s School for Gifted Youngsters|X-Mansion]] and prepare for their final jump into the present.{{r|Cable Vol 2 24}}\n\n[[File:Nathan Summers (Earth-616) and Hope Summers (Earth-616) say goodbye.jpg|left|thumb|190px|Hope says goodbye to her father, [[Nathan Summers (Earth-616)|Nathan]].]]\n===[[Second Coming]]===\nCable and Hope arrived at in the present at the ruins of the Xavier Institute. While searching the rubble for clues on the X-Men\'s current whereabouts, a team of [[Right (Earth-616)|Smiley Faces]] attacked them. They were able to escape, but now [[Bastion (Earth-616)|Bastion]] knew about the Mutant Messiah\'s return.{{r|X-Men: Second Coming #1}} Bastion began tracking the pair using Cable\'s [[Techno-Organic Virus|T.O. virus]] as a beacon. [[Cameron Hodge (Earth-616)|Hodge]]\'s Smiley-Faces and [[William Stryker (Earth-616)|Stryker]]\'s Purifiers both continued to pursue the pair, but the X-Men were also alerted to Hope and Cable\'s return via the [[Stepford Cuckoos (Earth-616)|Stepford Cuckoos]] and Cerebra.{{r|Uncanny X-Men #523}}{{r|New Mutants Vol 3 #12}}{{r|X-Men: Legacy #235}}\n\nA select team of X-Men was able to stop both the Purifiers and Smiley Faces, and catch up to Cable and Hope. Once the X-Men understood how Bastion was tracking Cable they broke into two teams: [[Kurt Wagner (Earth-616)|Nightcrawler]], Rogue and Hope teleporting back to [[Utopia (X-Men Base)|Utopia]] and Wolverine, Cable and the remainder of Alpha Team acting as decoys.{{r|X-Men: Legacy #235}} Bastion quickly uncovered the deception and attempted to kill Hope personally, but he was confronted by Rogue and then damaged when Nightcrawler sacrifices himself to save Hope by teleporting in one leap from [[Las Vegas]] to Utopia.\n[[File:The_X-Men_hold_of_Bastion\'s_attack.jpg|thumb|The X-Men hold of Bastion\'s attack.]]\nAfter Hope arrived on Utopia, Bastion launched the next phase of his plan. During the months leading up to Hope\'s return a large energy dome was built over the [[San Francisco|Bay Area]] to cut off the X-Men from escape or help. Once the dome was activated, Bastion opened a dimensional portal from his [[Earth-811|home reality]] to allow in more [[Nimrod (Earth-811)#Nimrod-Series Sentinel|Nimrod-Series Sentinels]].{{r|X-Men: Legacy #236}} Like the original Nimrod, these Sentinels are able to detect, analyze and adapt to mutant powers. They are also self-repairing. The X-Men were barely able to subdue them, and several X-Men sustained severe injuries.{{r|X-Force Vol 3 #27}} Every five minutes a wave of five new Nimrod Sentinels continued to appear through the portal.{{r|New Mutants Vol 3 #14}} Only by sending [[X-Force (Strike Team) (Earth-616)|X-Force]], Cable and [[Douglas Ramsey (Earth-616)|Cypher]] on a one-way mission into [[Earth-811|the future]] to reprogram and destroy the Nimrod Master Molds were the X-Men successful to defeating them.{{r|X-Force Vol 3 #27}}{{r|X-Men: Legacy #237}} However, to get X-Force home safely, Cable sacrificed his own life.{{r|X-Force Vol 3 #28}}\n\nOnce the dimensional portal was closed, Bastion decided it was time to confront Hope personally. He converted both [[Graydon Creed (Earth-616)|Graydon Creed]] and [[Stephen Lang (Earth-616)|Stephen Lang]] into robotic forms to battle the X-Men on the [[Golden Gate Bridge]]. Hope, grieving profusely at the death of her father, allowed her sorrow to turn into purposeful rage. Her mutant powers manifesting once more, Hope was able to draw on the mutant powers of the X-Men around her and single-handedly destroyed Bastion, Lang and Creed.{{r|X-Force Vol 3 #28}}\n\nAfter the battle, Hope laid down cradled in the remains of Cable\'s techno-organic arm and fell asleep for nearly 30 hours due to sheer exhaustion.{{r|X-Men: Second Coming #2}}\n\n[[File:Hope Summers (Earth-616) wants to go to Alaska.jpg|left|thumb|150px|Hope wants to find her family in [[Alaska]]]]\n===The Five Lights===\nOnce the dust had settled after the final battle with Bastion, Hope, accompanied by Rogue and [[James Bradley (Earth-616)|Dr. Nemesis]], was sent to the [[Baxter Building]] in [[New York City]] to be thoroughly examined by [[Reed Richards (Earth-616)|Mr. Fantastic]]. After the examination, Richards concluded that Hope showed no major signs damage from time-traveling. He did recommend she have some dental work done and begin her vaccination regiment. He also said what would be most helpful is a biological family history.{{r|Uncanny X-Men: The Heroic Age #1}}\n\nWhen Hope returned to Utopia, she was confronted by Cyclops. They agreed to not let Cable\'s death stand between them. Cyclops began to talk about Hope and a small group of X-Men visiting the five newly manifested mutants, but Hope refused to go. Cyclops realized he was expecting too much from Hope, and per her request promised to send her and a few X-Men to Cooperstown, Alaska to search for clues of her biological family{{r|Uncanny X-Men: The Heroic Age #1}}\n\nHope with Rogue, Cypher and Dr. Nemesis went to Alaska, and discovered that Hope\'s mother was [[Louise Spalding (Earth-616)|Captain Louise Spalding]] of the Cooperstown Fire Department. While visiting Louise\'s grave, Hope met her own grandmother, who told Hope about Louise.\n\nImmediately after leaving Alaska, Hope and the others headed to [[Vancouver]], [[Canada]] to save \"[[Laurie Tromette (Earth-616)|the first light]]\". Hope arrived just in time to save Laurie\'s life and stabilize her powers. After that, Laurie committed to follow Hope to the ends of the [[Earth]].{{r|Uncanny X-Men #526}} From Canada, Hope and the others went to [[Mexico City]], [[Mexico]] where Hope similarly saved [[Gabriel Cohuelo (Earth-616)|Gabriel Cohuelo]].{{r|Uncanny X-Men #527}}\n\nNext Hope accompanied by [[Ororo Munroe (Earth-616)|Storm]] traveled to [[Nigeria]] to save [[Idie Okonkwo (Earth-616)|Idie Okonkwo]] from a paramilitary group threatening to kill her. Hope stabilized her powers and brought her back to Utopia with the others?{{r|Uncanny X-Men #528}}\n\nThe next light was originally located in the [[Ukraine]], but when Hope, Rogue and the other lights arrived in [[Kiev]], he was gone. They tracked him over most of [[Europe]] and finally found in in [[Miami Beach]], [[Florida]]. Like the other lights, Hope was able to stabilize [[Teon Macik (Earth-616)|Teon]]\'s powers, and unlike the other she also \"tamed\" him?{{r|Uncanny X-Men #529}} After Teon joined, they group set off for [[Japan]] to stop the [[Kenji Uedo (Earth-616)|fifth light]] from destroying [[Tokyo]].{{r|Generation Hope #1}}\n\nAt first, Hope was unable to get close enough to touch Kenji, but she was able to control her powers enough to mimic Kenji although the strain of mimicking his powers made her faint with exhaustion.{{r|Generation Hope #2}} Cyclops then ordered the lights and Hope to stand back while the X-Men handled Kenji. Ignoring this order, Hope convinced the lights to help her save Kenji. She was able to again mimic Kenji\'s powers and use them to successfully subdue Kenji so she could physically touch him which resulted in the stabilization of both his powers and personality.{{r|Generation Hope #3}}\n\n[[File:Hope Summers (Earth-616) and the Sixth Light.png|thumb|left|Hope tries, and fails, to calm the Sixth Light.]]\n===The Sixth and Seventh Lights===\nAfter the incident in Tokyo, Cyclops replaced Rogue with [[Katherine Pryde (Earth-616)|Kitty Pryde]] as his envoy to the team. As a newly officially sanctioned X-Men team, the [[Lights (Earth-616)|Lights]] were deployed to [[Germany]], where a [[Sixth Light (Earth-616)|sixth light]] had activated. They discovered the the new light has in fact an unborn child who [[Telepathy|telepathically]] took control of those near him. Kenji and Teon proved immune to its power, and Kenji was able to create links to the rest of the lights to protect them as well. Laurie theorized that the child was acting out because it did not want to be born, and so Hope had Kenji link them to the baby. After several attempts to reason with it, Teon managed to calm the baby, and he was successfully delivered. Hope touched him, stabilizing his powers. The Lights then left Germany to return to Utopia; Teon\'s family had started legal action to regain custody of him.{{r|Generation Hope #6|#7}}\n\nWhile awaiting the trial, Hope was furious with the blas√© attitude taken by [[Kavita Rao (Earth-616)|Dr. Rao]] and [[Evangeline Whedon (Earth-616)|Evangeline Whedon]] Teon\'s custody. In an effort to distract her team from the looming legal proceedings, Hope insisted on adopting code names. Later despite his normally animalistic nature, Teon was able to eloquently offer a sound case of why he needed to stay with Hope and the X-Men. Immediately after the trial, Laurie and Kenji began to speculate on the reason all of the Lights (themselves included) seemed to be so drawn to following Hope.{{r|Generation Hope #8}}\n\nAfter the events in Germany and Teon\'s trial, Hope and her team continued to train and prepare for more new mutant activation\'s. Thanks to the Stepford Cuckoos monitoring in Cerebra, Hope and the Lights were alerted almost immediately of activation of the [[Zeeshan (Earth-616)|Seventh Light]]\'s powers. They left quickly, but arrived just after Zee had committed suicide. The whole team took the death very hard.{{r|Generation Hope #9}}\n\n===Fear Itself===\nLaurie and Idie decided to confront Hope and force her to take a break from her constant training. The trio went shopping in [[San Francisco]] and was ambushed by [[Frank Bohannan (Earth-616)|Crimson Commando]], who kidnapped Hope. Wolverine tracked her down and rescued her. This allowed Hope to confront him on why he\'s avoided her, and Wolverine shared his fear of the potential of eventually having to kill her, which Hope respected.{{r|Uncanny X-Men #540}}\n\nWhen [[Cain Marko (Earth-616)|Kuurth]], one of the [[Cul Borson (Earth-616)|Serpent]]\'s [[Worthy (Earth-616)|Worthy]], was marching on to destroy San Francisco and Utopia, Hope was a vital part of Cyclops second plan. After the initial attempt to stop Kuurth failed, Cyclops instructed Hope to utilize the power of other X-Men to remove Kuurth helmet. She was successful, but Kuurth proved more difficult to stop than the regular Juggernaut.{{r|Uncanny X-Men #541}} Kuurth was eventually driven off by [[Piotr Rasputin (Earth-616)|Colossus]], who had become the new Juggernaut.{{citation}}\n\n[[File:Hope Summers (Earth-616) Laurie Tromette (Earth-616) Generation Hope Vol 1 10.png|thumb|right|Laurie and Hope argue]]\n===Schism===\nAfter Idie killed the attacking [[Hellfire Club (Earth-616)|Hellfire Club]] at the Mutant History Museum, she argued with Laurie whether it could have been prevented. Laurie also disagreed with Hope on the issue of whether to remain on Utopia or not, but Hope forced her to stay. In the aftermath, Laurie insisted that Idie be made to go with Wolverine; Hope relented.{{citation}}\n\nHope\'s relationship with Gabriel was cut short when she discovered him kissing [[Megan Gwynn (Earth-616)|Pixie]]. However, Hope harbored no ill will towards Pixie and invited her to join the Lights.{{citation}}\n\n===Regenesis===\nHope and her team thought that they had found a new Light, but instead found [[Sebastian Shaw (Earth-616)|Sebastian Shaw]] who had previously been mind-wiped by [[Emma Frost (Earth-616)|Emma Frost]] and now had no memory of his past. Hope brought him back to Utopia and convinced Cyclops to allow him to join her team. Later, Kenji put his plans to betray her into motion and attacked her and the rest of the Lights. With help from [[Martha Johansson (Earth-616)|No-Girl]], they managed to kill him.{{citation}} \n\n===Avengers vs. X-Men===\nWhile the [[Avengers (Earth-616)|Avengers]] were massing and traveling to Utopia, Hope was training rigorously with Cyclops. After Cyclops pushed her too far, she manifested the Phoenix Fire Bird and sent him flying. Their training session was interrupted by the arrival of [[Captain America (Steven Rogers)|Captain America]] who demanded that the X-Men turn over Hope to the Avengers. Cyclops refused and blasted him which caused the Avengers to attack.{{r|Avengers vs. X-Men #1}} Hope was taken out of the battle but dispatched her Lights teammates and Wolverine and [[Spider-Man (Peter Parker)|Spider-Man]] who came to capture her, and proceeded to flee Utopia hoping to lure away the Avengers.{{r|Avengers vs. X-Men #2}} She scrambled her signals which made her seem to be in five places at once to prevent the X-Men or the Avengers from finding her. She tracked down Wolverine who was left in [[Antarctica]] by Captain America and offered him a deal. She was planning to travel to the [[Luna (Moon)|Moon]] in order to confront the [[Phoenix Force (Earth-616)|Phoenix]] but wanted Wolverine with her to stop her if she lost control. Wolverine betrayed her, however, and summoned the Avengers and shortly afterwards the X-Men arrived. Before the two groups could start fighting, the Phoenix finally arrived.{{r|Avengers vs. X-Men #4}} \n\nAfter being attacked by [[Iron Man (Anthony \"Tony\" Stark)|Iron Man]] the Phoenix breaks into five pieces and chooses Cyclops, Emma Frost, [[Illyana Rasputina (Earth-616)|Magik]], [[Namor McKenzie (Earth-616)|Namor]] and Colossus as its hosts. The unconscious Hope is taken back to Earth by the [[Phoenix Five (Earth-616)|Phoenix Five]] who go about reshaping the Earth into a better place to live for all.{{citation}}\n\nHope continued to hear the Phoenixes voice calling to her however, and when Cyclops asks her if she would accept the Phoenix Force now, she eagerly responds yes. Cyclops doesn\'t give it to her however, stating that she proved herself unworthy when she denied it on the Moon. The Avengers broke into to Utopia in order to capture her so as to better study the Phoenix Force, but they were stopped by the arrival of Cyclops and Emma. The [[Wanda Maximoff (Earth-616)|Scarlet Witch]] showed up as well however and Hope voluntarily went with her.{{citation}}\n\nShe was taken to the mystical city of [[K\'un-Lun]] and received the prophecy that she will be trained by Spider-Man who was puzzled as to what he was supposed to be teaching her. She was initially outraged over her new teachers lack of knowledge and seriousness but was quickly won over and began to listen, after he told her how he got his powers and that his uncle always told him \"With great power comes great responsibility\".{{citation}}\n\nHope\'s training was interrupted, however, when Cyclops, now empowered due to receiving more Phoenix portions after two more of his fellow Phoenixes fell, managed to penetrate the wall between K\'un-Lun and the regular world. Cyclops made short work of all the Avengers that opposed him, even managing to defeat [[Shou-Lao (Earth-616)|Shou-Lao]], the dragon that gives K\'un-Lun its power. Hope managed to stop him by copying both the dragon\'s flames and the Scarlet Witch\'s hex bolts, and used them to incapacitate him and send him to the Moon. Afterwards, when Cyclops became Dark Phoenix, Hope and the Scarlet Witch fought for a while because Hope believed Wanda ruined her life when she decreased the mutant race during the [[House of M]] event. Captain America and Iron Man broke up the fight and later created a plan to defeat Cyclops. During the fight, Hope and Wanda went head to head with Cyclops by using chaos magic with Shou-Lao kung fu to hurt Cyclops. [[Jean Grey (Earth-616)|Jean Grey]] came to Cyclops from the [[White Hot Room]] to help him let go of the Phoenix Force. When it did, Hope became its host and took away the flames of Dark Phoenix, becoming the White Phoenix. Wanda talked to Hope on understand her true purpose as the Phoenix. With their powers combined, they both said \"No More Phoenix\", which broke the original spell \"No More Mutants\" and brought back the mutant race. The Phoenix Force was presumed dead but there is no evidence to show what really happened. Cyclops was then taken to a prison and Hope had returned to her normal life. She attended the Jean Grey School for higher learning.{{citation}}\n\n===Consequences===\nAfter the events of Avengers vs X-Men she received a letter from her adoptive father Cable telling her at the end not to go looking for him, but burned the letter. Captain America and the Scarlet Witch went to her and suggested that she could go to the Jean Grey School for Higher Learning. She agrees, believing that this will give her a normal life since completing her destiny as Phoenix. After arriving at the school, she was thinking about the Five Lights, and how they would know what to do after the time as Phoenix. In the night, she began sneaking around parts of the world looking for her father Cable. When Utopia fell into the seas she went to take a look, and was confronted by Namor about why she was there, to which she replied the truth. Hope asked how he was after he had possessed the Phoenix and destroyed [[Wakanda]]. He said it was just war, and he did what he had to do, angering her into leaving him behind. Continuing her search, she was confronted by the Avengers, who asked where she had been. Before she could respond, the talk was interrupted when [[Jessica Drew (Earth-616)|Spider-Woman]] said there was a prison escape that led Cyclops to be freed, engineered by [[Danger (Earth-616)|Danger]], [[Max Eisenhardt (Earth-616)|Magneto]], and Magik. She returned to the school and found a note to look out the window. She saw Cable for the first time after the event and said he will be there for her when the time is right, after which they said their goodbyes and she went to sleep at last.{{citation}}\n\n[[File:Hope Summers (Earth-616) from Cable and X-Force Vol 1 13 cover.jpg|thumb|left]]\n===Cable and X-Force===\nHope has been living a \'normal life\' for four weeks now. She speaks to a psychiatrist named Doctor Townley due to The Avengers making the sessions mandatory. She now has foster parents that watch twenty-seven hours of television a week, and their excessive smiling makes her uncomfortable. She feels that her foster parents can\'t compare to Cable. [[Neena Thurman (Earth-616)|Domino]] is speaking to [[Tabitha Smith (Earth-616)|Boom Boom]] via communication link about how she made a sucker out of a client to pay her three times the amount for a job to rescue a professor from [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology|M.I.T.]] she considers \"easy money\". Turns out Hope had hacked into her files, and beat her to the punch. Domino is surprised to see Hope again. Hope makes a deal with trade the missing professor for her luck powers to find Cable. Domino and Hope locate Cable in a junkyard in [[Nebraska]]. She becomes enraged and mimics Cable\'s telekinesis. She explains that while she was looking all over the world for him, he was there and didn\'t bother to reach out to her the minute he woke up from his coma. Cable responds with \"I miss you too kid. Every damned day\". Hope\'s rage stops and she hugs him. Suddenly Cable has another headache and Hope sees visions of a future event, Cable passes out and awakens later on, only to see Hope\'s vision on television.\n\nHope later joins Cable\'s X-Force and fight with him against [[Nathan Summers (Stryfe) (Earth-4935)|Stryfe]] and confront Bishop, who is back in the present and member of [[X-Force (Strike Team) (Earth-616)|another X-Force team]]. At the end of the battle, the two teams are disband.\n\nAt the graduation day of the Jean Grey school, Hope makes a surprise visit to see Idie.{{r|X-Force Vol 4 2}}\n\n===New X-Force and MeMe===\nAfter a huge disaster occurred in [[Alexandria (Virginia)|Alexandria]], [[Virginia]], Hope became comatose due to the nature of the blast. This led to her father Cable to reform another X-Force team. During the team\'s first outing, they were able to save a new mutant named [[MeMe (Mutant) (Earth-616)|MeMe]], who also was stuck in a catatonic state. Unbeknownst to them, MeMe was brain dead but still alive to the point where Hope was able to mimic her mutant abilities of electro-magnetic transference and decided to impersonate MeMe in order to stay close to her father.{{r|X-Force Vol 4 1}}\n\nShe began to help X-Force as a digital interface to override the doors locking mechanism with her [[Homo superior|mutant]] abilities, which allowed Cable to access the door so that he could eliminate their target [[Qareen (Earth-616)|Qareen]], in exchange for the information from [[Fiqh (Earth-616)|Fiqh]] about who was turning mutants into weapons.{{r|X-Force Vol 4 2}} \n\nMeme next shows up with her X-Force teammates in northwestern [[Brazil]] to locate a mutant named [[Antonio Aggasiz (Earth-616)|Antonio Aggasiz]] who was targeted by arms dealer [[Yevgeny Malevitch (Earth-616)|Volga]] for his dimensional teleporting abilities. Unable to scan the compound due to psi-dampeners, Meme and the team infiltrate the place using her abilities to hack into and override the computer systems and doors, while [[Elizabeth Braddock (Earth-616)|Psylocke]] handled the soldiers. \n\nAs they entered the building, they noticed multiple mutants being held captive but no Antonio. Meme digitally scanned the remaining areas until she located his signal in a separate room. They came in to see a frightened and paranoid Antonio strapped down to a chair, while screaming out the name Volga. Volga then showed up behind X-Force taking every member out including Meme with concentrated energy blasts. After that he incinerated Antonio on the spot before they could get him to talk.{{r|X-Force Vol 4 3}}\n\nAfter being captured by Volga, X-Force was rescued by Cable and [[James Bradley (Earth-616)|Dr. Nemesis]]. As the group retreated back to their base Psylocke was able to telepathically read MeMe\'s mind revealing that she was really Hope in disguise. Hope begged her not to tell her father, because this was the only way she could be close to him.{{r|X-Force Vol 4 6}}\n\nAfter Fantomex became crazy by his compulsion to become the best there is, X-Force found Mojo, who revealed to Cable that Hope has been disguised as MeMe all along.{{citation}}\n\n| Powers                  = \n[[File:Hope Summers using her powers.jpg|right|thumb|190px|Hope Summers using her powers.]]\n[[File:Hope Summers (Earth-616) battles Bastion (Earth-616).jpg|right|thumb|150px|Hope uses [[Scott Summers (Earth-616)|Cyclops]]\' optic blast against [[Bastion (Earth-616)|Bastion]].]]\n[[File:Hope Summers (Earth-616) with psionic exo armor.jpg|right|thumb|150px|Hope Summers using [[Hisako Ichiki (Earth-616)|Armor]]\'s [[Hisako Ichiki (Earth-616)#Powers|Psionic exo-armor]].]]\n\nHope Summers is an \'\'\'[[Mutant Power Level Classification#Omega Level Mutants|Omega level]] [[Homo superior|mutant]]\'\'\'.{{r|X-Men: Phoenix Force Handbook #1}} She was born with the following powers:\n\n====\'\'\'Pluripotent Echopraxia\'\'\'{{r|X-Force Vol 4 6}}====\nHope can psychically duplicate the power-signature of mutants physically near her.{{r|Uncanny X-Men #541}}{{r|X-Force Vol 4 6}} Although she does require close proximity to subjects, she does not need to physically touch them (as with [[Rogue (Anna Marie) (Earth-616)|Rogue]]), nor does it appear as though her using a subject\'s powers deplete their own power level. Additionally, Hope can duplicate multiple power-signatures concurrently with seemingly no limit.{{r|Uncanny X-Men #541}} However, her duplicated powers fade due to time, distance, and usage.{{r|Cable and X-Force #9}}{{r|Cable and X-Force #15}} She is only able to duplicate mutant powers, not those of other metahumans.{{r|Avengers vs. X-Men #0}} The upper-limits of her powers have yet to be reached or determined.{{r|X-Men: Legacy #263}} The powers Hope has demonstrated so far include:\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'Power and Aura Absorption:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Rogue (Anna Marie) (Earth-616)|Rogue]]. She touched Rogue and survived without any damage and erased all of the previous memories and abilities Rogue had absorbed, including those of the Hecatomb. She also cured Rogue of the Strain 88 virus.{{r|New X-Men Vol 2 46}} In other words, she did \'\'\"reset [her] powers\"\'\'.{{r|{{c|Marvel Fact Files #2}}; [[Rogue (Anna Marie) (Earth-616)|Rogue]]\'s entry}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'[[Telekinesis]] and [[Telepathy]]:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Nathan Summers (Earth-616)|Cable]]. Using telekinesis, she was able to stop a bullet in midair, and she was able to sense Bishop\'s presence using telepathy.{{r|Cable Vol 2 21}} When she was finally reunited with her father, she again mimicked his telekinesis and upon contact with him may have briefly gain precognition.{{r|Cable and X-Force #1}} Hope was briefly an \'\'\'[[Mutant Power Level Classification#Omega Level Telekinetics|Omega Level Telekinetic]]\'\'\' after having stabbed [[Nathan Summers (Earth-616)|Cable]] with the [[Psimitar]].{{r|Cable and X-Force #14}} Cable\'s telekinesis spilled out and was absorbed by Hope,{{r|Cable and X-Force #16}} stored and used for weeks, allowing her to form force-fields,{{r|Cable and X-Force #15}} telekinetic superhuman-strength{{r|Cable and X-Force #16}} and \"\'\'\'Omega-Level Mind Bullets\'\'\'\".{{r|Cable and X-Force #17}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'Energy Absorption and Concussive Blasts:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Lucas Bishop (Earth-1191)|Bishop]]. Absorbed and re-channeled a concussive blast at Bishop while he was hunting her.{{r|Cable Vol 2 21}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'Optic Blasts:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Scott Summers (Earth-616)|Cyclops]]. Exhibited once when Hope yelled at Cyclops for sending Cable into the future without a way back{{r|Uncanny X-Men #525}} and again displayed it while battling [[Bastion (Earth-616)|Bastion]].{{r|X-Force Vol 3 #28}} Hope later displayed this power while furious with [[Evangeline Whedon (Earth-616)|Evangeline Whedon]] in Cyclops\' presence.{{r|Generation Hope #8}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'Organic Steel Transformation:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Piotr Rasputin (Earth-616)|Colossus]]. Used while battling Bastion to punch through his torso.{{r|X-Force Vol 3 #28}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'[[Force Field|Psionic Exo-Armor]]:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Hisako Ichiki (Earth-616)|Armor]]. Used while battling [[Bastion (Earth-616)|Bastion]] to deflect his blasts.{{r|X-Force Vol 3 #28}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'Cryokinesis/[[Thermokinesis]]:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Robert Drake (Earth-616)|Iceman]] (or possibly [[Ororo Munroe (Earth-616)|Storm]]). Used while battling Bastion, to create a pillar of ice and temporarily freeze him.{{r|X-Force Vol 3 #28}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'[[Electrokinesis]]:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Noriko Ashida (Earth-616)|Surge]] (or possibly [[Ororo Munroe (Earth-616)|Storm]]). Used while battling Bastion.{{r|X-Force Vol 3 #28}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'[[Geokinesis]]:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Amara Aquilla (Earth-616)|Magma]] (or possibly [[Santo Vaccarro (Earth-616)|Rockslide]]). Used while battling Bastion.{{r|X-Force Vol 3 #28}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'[[Telekinetic]] creation of biological matter and ferrous material:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Kenji Uedo (Earth-616)|Kenji Uedo]]. Used in [[Tokyo]] when trying to save Kenji when his powers first manifest. This is also the first time Hope consciously used her mutant powers.{{r|Generation Hope #2}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'[[Superhuman Strength]] and [[Flight|Self-Propelled Flight]]:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Namor McKenzie (Earth-616)|Namor]]. Used to subdue Namor during his delirium in the [[Negative Zone]]. Hope also sprouted Namor\'s signature vestigial \"wings\" on both of her ankles while mimicking his powers.{{r|Namor: The First Mutant Annual #1}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'[[Healing Factor|Regenerative Healing Factor]]:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Wolverine (James \"Logan\" Howlett)|Wolverine]]. Used to heal a black eye, several gunshot wounds to her shins and to regrow her nose, eyes and mend several cuts during her abduction by [[Frank Bohannan (Earth-616)|Crimson Commando]].{{r|Uncanny X-Men #539}}\n\n[[File:Hope Summers (Earth-616) Uncanny X-Men Vol 1 541.png|thumb|right|Hope draws on the powers of [[Megan Gwynn (Earth-616)|Pixie]], [[Laurie Tromette (Earth-616)|Transonic]], [[Santo Vaccarro (Earth-616)|Rockslide]], [[Max Eisenhardt (Earth-616)|Magneto]] and [[Nezhno Abidemi (Earth-616)|Gentle]] to face [[Cain Marko (Earth-616)|Kuurth]]]]\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'Pixie Wings:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Megan Gwynn (Earth-616)|Pixie]]. Used while attempting to remove the helmet of [[Cain Marko (Earth-616)|Kuurth]].{{r|Uncanny X-Men #541}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'[[Superhuman Speed|Transonic Speed]] and Shifting Crystal Skin:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Laurie Tromette (Earth-616)|Transonic]]. Used while attempting to remove the helmet of Kuurth.{{r|Uncanny X-Men #541}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'Inorganic Rock Form:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Santo Vaccarro (Earth-616)|Rockslide]]. Used while attempting to remove the helmet of Kuurth.{{r|Uncanny X-Men #541}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'Magnetokinesis:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Max Eisenhardt (Earth-616)|Magneto]]. Used while attempting to remove the helmet of Kuurth.{{r|Uncanny X-Men #541}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'[[Superhuman Strength|Extreme Strength]]:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Nezhno Abidemi (Earth-616)|Gentle]]. Used while attempting to remove the helmet of Kuurth.{{r|Uncanny X-Men #541}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'[[Teleportation]]:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Illyana Rasputina (Earth-616)|Magik]]. Used to teleport to a vantage point and shoot [[Nathaniel Essex (Earth-616)|Sinister]] in the forehead.{{r|Uncanny X-Men Vol 2 2}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'Organic Diamond Form and [[Telepathy]]:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Emma Frost (Earth-616)|Emma Frost]]. Used to shield herself from mind control by Sinister, and later to communicated while Emma was trapped in her diamond form while battling the Sinister-controlled [[Tiamut (Earth-616)|Dreaming Celestial]].{{r|Uncanny X-Men Vol 2 #2|3}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'[[Telekinesis|Telekinetic flight]] and [[Pyrokinesis]]:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Bennet du Paris (Earth-616)|Exodus]] (or possibly [[Rachel Summers (Earth-811)|Marvel Girl]]). Used when battling Exodus with Wolverine\'s X-Men.{{r|X-Men: Legacy #263}} \n\n*\'\'\'\'\'Increased Size and Strength:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Gordon Fraley (Earth-616)|Puff Adder]]. Used when stopping the [[Serpent Society (Earth-616)|Serpent Society]]\'s bank robbery.{{r|Avengers vs. X-Men #0}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'Bone Claws:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Wolverine (James \"Logan\" Howlett)|Wolverine]]. Used to fight against the [[Shi\'ar Death Commandos (Earth-616)|Death Commandos]].{{r|Wolverine & the X-Men #11}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'[[Telepathy]]:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Rachel Summers (Earth-811)|Marvel Girl]]. Used when Marvel Girl was tracking Hope for Cyclops and the [[Phoenix Five (Earth-616)|Phoenix Five]].{{r|Wolverine & the X-Men #12}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'Breathing Fire:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Shou-Lao (Earth-616)|Shou-Lao]]. Used when fighting [[Scott Summers (Earth-616)|Cyclops]]. This is the first and (so far) only time Hope\'s been able to mimic the powers of a non-mutant. (although this was more due to her absorbing his power, which is the same as that of Iron Fist){{r|Avengers vs. X-Men #10}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'Hex Bolts:\'\'\'\'\' from the [[Wanda Maximoff (Earth-616)|Scarlet Witch]]. Used when fighting the [[Phoenix Force (Earth-616)|Phoenix]]-empowered [[Scott Summers (Earth-616)|Cyclops]].{{r|Avengers vs. X-Men #10}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'X-Ray Vision:\'\'\'\'\' from closet mutant in physics class. Accidentally used while at boarding school.{{r|Cable and X-Force #1}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'Luck Manipulation:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Neena Thurman (Earth-616)|Domino]]. Used to find Cable.{{r|Cable and X-Force #1}} \n\n*\'\'\'\'\'Pheromonal Mind Manipulation:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Kara Killgrave (Earth-616)|Purple Woman]]. Used to evade the [[Avengers Unity Division (Earth-616)|Uncanny Avengers]].{{r|Cable and X-Force #9}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'Telepathic Illusions:\'\'\'\'\' from [[Martinique Wyngarde (Earth-616)|Mastermind (Martinique Wyngarde)]]. Used to evade the [[Avengers Unity Division (Earth-616)|Uncanny Avengers]].{{r|Cable and X-Force #9}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'Sentient Data Form, Cyberpathy, and Electro-Magnetic Transference:\'\'\'\'\' from [[MeMe (Mutant) (Earth-616)|MeMe]]. Currently Hope is secretly mimicking MeMe\'s powers and assuming her identity to allow herself better assess and to be closer to Cable and his X-Force.{{r|X-Force Vol 4 6}} \n\n===Other Powers===\n[[File:Messiah Baby 002.jpg|right|thumb|150px|Hope Summers with Phoenix eyes]]\n[[File:Hope Summers (Earth-616) and Phoenix Force (Earth-616) 03.jpg|right|thumb|150px|Hope Summers with Phoenix eyes]]\n[[File:Avengers_Vs_X_Men_12_Hope_Summers_(Earth-616).jpg|thumb|150px|Hope Summers as the Phoenix]]\n====\'\'\'[[Phoenix Force (Earth-616)|Phoenix Force]]\'\'\'====\nHope has demonstrated a flaming energy aura like the [[Phoenix Force (Earth-616)|Phoenix raptor]] several times, even as early as five months old.{{r|Cable Vol 2 5}}{{r|X-Men: Hope #1}}{{r|X-Force Vol 3 #28}}{{r|X-Men: Second Coming #2}} These manifestations could suggest she is a potential avatar for the Phoenix. After Cable\'s return from the future and being consumed by the techno-organic virus, Hope absorbed the virus and used the Phoenix flames to destroy the virus and cure Cable. Cable then told Cyclops that Hope was the Phoenix.{{r|Avengers: X-Sanction #4}} The Scarlet Witch said that Hope is a part of Phoenix.\n\nAs the Phoenix comes nearer to Earth, Hope has been able to feel its presence and exhibit the following powers:{{r|Avengers vs. X-Men #2|#4}}\n*\'\'\'\'\'Cosmic Pyrokinesis:\'\'\'\'\' Hope has created cosmic flames often under duress, but with increasing control.\n*\'\'\'\'\'Concussive Force Blasts:\'\'\'\'\' Hope has wielded this energy to project beams of immense concussive force.\n*\'\'\'\'\'Resurrection Force:\'\'\'\'\' Despite being fatally stabbed by the Shi\'Ar Death Commandos, Hope was almost immediately revived by the Phoenix Force, with all of her injuries healed.\n*\'\'\'\'\'Immortality:\'\'\'\'\' Hope cannot die, as the Phoenix will resurrect her if she sustains a fatal injury.\n\n*\'\'\'Phoenix Force Avatar:\'\'\' When Hope finally became one with Phoenix Force she was able to use all of the Phoenix\'s powers. Though Hope is Phoenix it is unsure how strong she is compared to previous Phoenix hosts, such as Jean Grey. While bonded with the Phoenix, Hope gained the title White Phoenix, implying some connection to the Phoenix or Jean who took the title White Phoenix Of The Crown implying that Jean could still be more powerful then Hope.\n\n====\'\'\'Psychic Energy\'\'\' and \'\'\'Undetectablity\'\'\'====\nIt is also notable that after Hope\'s initial detection at birth, [[Cerebra (Mutant Detector)|Cerebra]] blew up.{{r|X-Men: Messiah Complex #1}} After repairs were made the [[Stepford Cuckoos (Earth-616)|Three-in-One]] tried to search for her because she had been kidnapped by the [[Marauders (Earth-616)|Marauders]] yet she somehow became undetectable by mutant-detecting equipment. It is possible, however, that she was merely being shielded by Cable, as he was with her from the time she left the hospital until he left to stop the [[Nimrod (Earth-811)|Nimrod-Series Sentinels]].{{r|X-Force Vol 3 #27|#28}}\n\nHope was again able to disguise her signal when both the X-Men and [[Avengers (Earth-616)|Avengers]] were looking across the globe for her, through the use of a device Cable taught her to build.{{r|Avengers vs. X-Men #3|#4}}\n\n====\'\'\'The Five Lights\'\'\'====\nAlso, soon after Hope\'s return to the [[Earth-616|present]], [[Lights (Earth-616)|five]] new [[X-Gene|X-Genes]] manifested across the globe. Besides her own birth, these are the first new manifestations of [[Homo superior|mutant powers]] since [[Decimation|M-Day]].{{r|X-Men: Second Coming #2}} More new mutants have continued to manifest, but slower than the original five.{{r|Generation Hope #6}}\n*\'\'\'\'\'X-Gene Stabilization:\'\'\'\'\' All of the mutants activated between the events of the [[Second Coming]] and [[Avengers vs. X-Men]] displayed wildly unstable powers. The only thing the seems to stabilize the new mutants powers is direct contact with Hope.{{r|Uncanny X-Men #526|#529}}{{r|Generation Hope #3}}{{r|Generation Hope #7}}\n\n*\'\'\'\'\'Influence\'\'\'\'\' & \'\'\'Lights Bonding:\'\'\' The Lights were shown to be linked each other and to the new activation\'s, with some low level control from Hope over them. Hope has exhibited some subconscious low level of persuasion or manipulation over the post-M-Day new mutants.{{r|Generation Hope #8}}{{r|Generation Hope #11}}{{r|Generation Hope #15|17}} All the Lights were also affected by the suicide of [[Zeeshan (Earth-616)|Zeeshan]].{{r|Generation Hope #9}} That situation was witnessed by Laurie and [[Kenji Uedo (Earth-616)|Kenji]],{{r|Generation Hope #8}} and later by [[Katherine Pryde (Earth-616)|Kitty Pryde]].{{r|Generation Hope #12}} Also, when the [[Sixth Light (Earth-616)|Sixth Light]] activated, all of the Lights were able to sense it.{{r|Generation Hope #6}}\n\n{{New Power Grid\n| Reference         = \n| Intelligence      = 5\n| Strength          = 4\n| Speed             = 5\n| Durability        = 4\n| Energy Projection = 5\n| Fighting Skills   = 5\n| Explanation       = \n}}\n\n\n| Abilities               = Hope has learned to fight from Cable by observing him. Hope was further tutored in survival techniques, various hand-held firearms and blades, stealth, CPR, combat first-aid, warfare strategy, and some gymnastics.\n| Strength                = Possesses the strength of a normal girl her age, height, and build who engages in extreme regular exercise (although this can vary, depending on what powers she has access to)\n| Weaknesses              = Hope\'s mutant powers are not fully under control and generates power levels that are potentially dangerous to people and environments around her.\n\nHope\'s ability to mimic superpowers is limited to [[Homo superior|mutants]] only.{{r|Avengers vs. X-Men #0}} Therefore, she cannot duplicate the abilities of non-mutant superpowered beings (i.e. [[Peter Parker (Earth-616)|Spider-Man]], [[Luke Cage (Earth-616)|Luke Cage]], or the [[Fantastic Four (Earth-616)|Fantastic Four]]).\n\n| Equipment               = \n| Transportation          = [[X-Men Blackbird]], [[Illyana Rasputina (Earth-616)|Magik]], [[Megan Gwynn (Earth-616)|Pixie]]; formerly [[Nathan Summers (Earth-616)|Cable\'s]] time device; Terraforming Pods; \'\'[[Ensabahnur I]]\'\'.\n| Weapons                 = Usually some sort of firearms.\n\n| Notes                   = * Hope Summers was first \'\'\"prophesied\"\'\' in {{c|New X-Men Vol 2 36}}, her birth first mentioned in {{c|X-Men: Messiah Complex #1}}, first seen on-panel in {{c|X-Men Vol 2 205}} and named by [[Nathan Summers (Earth-616)|Cable]] in {{c|Cable Vol 2 10}}.\n* Hope has red hair, green eyes and a \"close\" relationship with the Phoenix. This has led some fans to assume that she is [[Jean Grey (Earth-616)|Jean Grey]] reincarnated, though this has not been confirmed in the comics.\n** [[Idie Okonkwo (Earth-616)|Oya]] thought that Hope looked a bit like [[Rachel Summers (Earth-811)|Rachel Summers]].{{r|Generation Hope #10}}', '', 'Secret', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
